## 4. Feature Specification

### 4.1 Brand Toggle

- **UI**: Two-button toggle bar (Apple | Samsung)
- **Behavior**: Filters `filteredParts` to only parts matching `activeBrand`
- **Default**: Apple
- **Accessibility**: `aria-pressed` on active button, `role="group"` on container

### 4.2 Omni-Search

- **Input**: Single text field, auto-focused
- **Logic**: AND matching
  - User types: `"15 pro battery"`
  - Splits to: `["15", "pro", "battery"]`
  - Matches part if **all three terms** appear in `searchIndex`
- **Case Sensitivity**: Case-insensitive (queries lowercased before matching)
- **Partial Matching**: YES (e.g., “15” matches “iphone15”, “i15”)
- **Debouncing**: None (client-side, no network calls)

### 4.3 Results Display

- **Grid Layout**: Responsive (1 col mobile, 2 col tablet, 3 col desktop)
- **Card Structure**:
  - SKU badge (cyan pill)
  - Stock status (green/“IN STOCK” or red/“OUT OF STOCK”)
  - Part name (Quality + Type)
  - Wholesale price (in USD, cents → dollars)
  - “Add to Cart” button (disabled if stock === 0)

### 4.4 Empty States

1. **Loading**: Spinner + “Loading catalog…” (shown while `loading === true`)
1. **Network Error**: Error message + “Retry” button (shown when `error !== null`)
1. **No Results**: Contextual message + “Clear search” button (shown when `filteredParts.length === 0` and search is active)

