## 6. Performance Characteristics

### Client-Side Filtering

- **Algorithm**: O(n) per keystroke (n = number of parts)
- **Optimization**: `useMemo` prevents re-computation if `parts`, `activeBrand`, or `searchQuery` haven’t changed
- **Scalability Limit**: ~5,000 parts before perceived lag on modern machines
- **Recommendation**: For catalogs > 10,000 SKUs, migrate to server-side filtering (see Section 7)

### Initial Load

- **Fetch Time**: Depends on `/api/parts` performance
- **No Pagination**: Currently, all parts fetched on mount. For large catalogs, implement pagination or lazy-loading.

-----

## 7. Scalability Roadmap

### Phase 1 (Current)

- Client-side filter for up to ~5,000 parts
- All parts fetched on mount (single request)
- No pagination

### Phase 2 (Recommended for CellTech v2)

- **Server-Side Filtering**:
  
  ```http
  GET /api/parts?brand=Apple&q=15%20pro
  ```
  
  Server returns only matching parts. Client requests subset.
- **Pagination**:
  
  ```http
  GET /api/parts?brand=Apple&limit=50&offset=0
  ```
- **Benefits**:
  - Instant search for large catalogs
  - Reduced initial payload
  - Can index full-text search DB (pg_trgm, Elasticsearch)

### Phase 3 (B2B Platform Maturity)

- Elasticsearch or Algolia integration for fuzzy matching, facets, typo tolerance
- Typeahead suggestions (popular searches, recent filters)
- Search analytics tracking

